- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper involves developing an AI model for molecular optimization. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although not directly related to computer vision, the paper involves learning to translate graphs, which is a common problem in computer vision and pattern recognition. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper involves natural language processing techniques such as adversarial training to align distributions of molecules. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper does not directly involve software engineering, but it may be relevant for developing software tools for molecular optimization.
